-- Alpha Says 2013 Coal Shipments 80 Million to 95 Million Tons
-- B y   S i m o n   C a s e y
-- 2012-11-13T12:27:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-13/alpha-says-2013-coal-shipments-80-million-to-95-million-tons.html
Alpha Natural Resources Inc. (ANR) , the
second-largest U.S. coal producer by sales, said its 2013
shipment volumes are expected to be about 80 million to 95
million tons.  Capital expenditure will be $300 million to $350 million
next year, the company said today in a filing.  The Bristol, Virginia-based company said Nov. 2 that
shipments will be 100 million to 115 million tons this year
while capital spending will be $450 million to $600 million.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Simon Casey in  New York  at 
